<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98595807669272></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98595807669272><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98595807669272>Armor Class is the most important</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98595807669272#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 30th 8:14 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The primary stat for an enchanter is - surprize Armor Class.<br><br>Intelligence affects your maximum mana provided you are able to med to full mana.&nbsp;&nbsp;It seems to me that if im in a group and I can med to full mana - something is wrong and im not getting good exp.  <br><br>If you have two containers, one holds a liter(200 int) and the other holds 3/4(150 int)  liter, one is no better than the other you only have 1/2 liter of fluid (mana) at a time.<br><br>Charisma is very important if you only use charms.  Dont get me wrong, charms are huge.  Some situations however they are too dangerous or impractical to use.<br><br>Armor Class is huge for an enchanter.  You take a beating as an enchanter and you dont have much probably dont have much hp.  Mobs HATE you.  Armor class will give your healer a few extra seconds to heal you when you you get a resist or you are using single target mezz and have more than one mobs that need mezzed.<br><br>In the end all three are very important.  As with many things in the enchanters life, balancing is a complex task.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
