	   <tr><td colspan=2>Intelegence is the most important attribute for all the "offensive" casters, as wisdom is for the "healing" casters. It controls how much mana ye have, has effect on broken concentration and fizzles, and controls how fast ye improve in the related skill of casting, among others. Charisma affects how well or long certain of the chanters spells will work, and the chanter has a larger line of charisma effected spells, but still Int effects all yer spells more where as charisma effects only some and to a lesser degree.<br><br>I have seen post here and else where, where chanters have gone into long testing ie: cast&nbsp;&nbsp;charm 100 times on same crit each with normal char and  int, then each with cha boosted 20 pts and they found only a slight increase in successes (like 4% i think).<br><br>Not to say thats not good, even a slight increase in this game can make a world of difference, but over all for a chhanter Int just effects to much in to many ways for it not to still be the most important attribute for a chanter, with cha being a good second.<br><br>Ifme chanter had a choice between 200 int or 200 cha, would be a nobrainer, definatly go with the 200 int.<br><br>Now for 200+, they have the soft cap on int, but Ive heard that they dont on cha, not sure just what Ive read and heard:)<br>&nbsp;<br>Fiddo Lupineopolus<br>Cazic Thule<br>What do you mean being lazy is no way to live?</td></tr>
